         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">In honour</supplied> of Durpius. To Aurelius Sempronius Severus, Roman Knight, leading citizen of Alexandria, 
               on account of the distinguished and admirable quality of his activities, in addition to tenures of the decurionate and a statue set up in his own city, 
               among the people of Lepcis Magna <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>
         
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Dulcitius! Ad Aurelius Sempronius Serenus, cavaliere romano, principalis di Alessandria, per il suo insigne e mirabile
               ingegno negli studi, oltre all’onore dei decurionati e alla statua collocata presso di sé, (anche) presso gli abitanti di Leptis
               Magna . . . </p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en">
            <p>(Statue of) Dulcitius. To Aurelius Sempronius Serenus, Roman knight, principalis of Alexandria, on account of the distinguished and admirable genius in studies, 
               in addition to the honour of the decurionates and the statue that was set up among themselves, also at Lepcis Magna . . . </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Aurelius Sempronius Serenus, signo Dulcitius: <title>PLRE</title> I, Serenus 3</p>
